nology Centre; K. Yoshimi, Tohoku University)\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Fluidization XIV: From Fundamentals To Products" href="http://www.engconf.org/staging/conferences/chemical-engineering/fluidization-xiv-from-fundamentals-to-products/">May 25-30, 2013</a> (13AF) FLUIDIZATION XIV: FROM FUNDAMENTALS TO PRODUCTS </strong> (Noordwijkerhout, The Netherlands)\r\n(J.A.M. Kuipers and N.G. Deen, TU Eindhoven; R.F. Mudde and J.R. van Ommen, Delft Univ. of Technology)\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Biochemical And Molecular Engineering XVIII" href="http://www.engconf.org/staging/conferences/biotechnology/biochemical-and-molecular-engineering-xviii/">June 16-20, 2013</a> (13AM) BIOCHEMICAL AND MOLECULAR ENGINEERING XVIII</strong> (Beijing, China)\r\n(Honorary Chairs: Daniel I.C. Wang, MIT; Pinkai Ouyang, Nanjing Chemical University; H. Zhao, Univ. of Illinois; D. Robinson, Merck)\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Advances In Optics For Biotechnology, Medicine And Surgery XIII" href="http://www.engconf.org/staging/conferences/biotechnology/advances-in-optics-for-biotechnology-medicine-and-surgery-xiii/">June TBD, 2013</a> (13AO) ADVANCES IN OPTICS FOR BIOTECHNOLOGY, MEDICINE AND SURGERY XIII</strong> (Lake Tahoe, California)\r\n(J.W. Tunnell, Univ. of Texas at Austin; M. Fitzmaurice, Case Western Univ.; A.C. Boccara, ESPCI-Paris Tech.)\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="From Pure To Doped Carbon-Based Nanomaterials" href="http://www.engconf.org/staging/conferences/materials-science-including-nanotechnology/from-pure-to-doped-carbon-based-nanomaterials/">Sept TBD, 2013</a> (13AD) FROM PURE TO DOPED CARBON-BASED NANOMATERIALS: RECENT ADVANCES AND APPLICATIONS</strong> (Lanzarote, C.I., Spain)\r\n(R. Arenal, Univ. of Zaragoza; C.P. Ewels, Univ. de Nantes; D. Goldberg, NIMS and Univ. of Tsukuba; V. Meunier, Rensselear Polytechnic Institute; M. Motta, Thomas Swan &amp; Co., Ltd.; R. Rubio, Max Planck Inst.)\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Nano- And Micromechanical Testing In Materials Research And Development IV